                    "updated": "2012-04-25T11:51:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50504",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The issue here is that Zend_Loader_PluginLoader supports namespaces in the class prefix (see ZF-7350), however one cannot load a class from a sub-namespace of the prefix namespace.  Test case which fails w\/ current implementation:\r\n{code}\r\n$loader = new Zend_Loader_PluginLoader(array());\r\n$loader->addPrefixPath('Zfns\\\\', dirname(__FILE__) . '\/_files\/Zfns');\r\n$className = $loader->load('Foo\\Bar');\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nI've tested the patch and verified that it works as advertised.  I've attached new patches as the OP's patches were in git format. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-07T00:32:33.000+0000",
